      "content": "The risk of the infection returning is not just a theoretical concern; it's a real possibility. Even if the infection seems completely gone, some bacteria can persist in your body. By stopping the antibiotics early, you might be leaving some of these bacteria behind, which can multiply and cause the infection to return, potentially more aggressively. The side effects you're experiencing are unfortunate, but the potential consequences of an untreated infection are far more serious. Trust that the benefits of completing your antibiotics outweigh the temporary discomfort you're feeling. Your health is the priority, and a few more days of medication can save you from a much bigger problem down the line.",
      "source": "target",
